'''休·杜兰特·怀特{{Post-nominals|country=GBR|FRS|FAA}}'''（{{Lang-en|Hugh Francis Durrant-Whyte}}，{{Bd|1961年|2月6日}}）是一位英裔[[澳大利亚|澳大利亚]][[工程师|工程师]]和[[学者|学者]]。他因在机器人概率方法领域的开创性工作而闻名。自20世纪90年代初期开始，他的团队基于[[SLAM|SLAM]]开发的算法，使得汽车在自动驾驶时，即使传感器读数存在噪声，也能够处理不确定性并对自身定位。

==早年生活与求学阶段==
杜兰特·怀特出生于英国[[伦敦|伦敦]]。他曾就读于[[理查德·黑尔学校|理查德·黑尔学校]]——当时是赫特福德郡赫特福德的一所州立文法学校。他在伦敦大学学习工程学，并于1983年获得一级理学学士学位。随后，他移居美国，在宾夕法尼亚大学学习系统工程。他于1985年获得[[工程学硕士|工程学硕士]]学位，并于1986年获得[[博士|博士]]学位<ref name="whoswho" />。他于1983年获得[[图伦奖|图伦奖]]<ref name=":0" />。

He was educated at [[Richard_Hale_School|Richard Hale School]], then a [[State_school|state]] [[grammar_school|grammar school]] in [[Hertford|Hertford]], Hertfordshire. He studied engineering at the [[University_of_London|University of London]], graduating with a [[First_class_honours|first class]] [[Bachelor_of_Science|Bachelor of Science]] (BSc) degree in 1983. He then moved to the United States where he studied [[systems_engineering|systems engineering]] at the [[University_of_Pennsylvania|University of Pennsylvania]]: he graduated with a [[Master_of_Science_in_Engineering|Master of Science in Engineering]] (MSE) degree in 1985 and a [[Doctor_of_Philosophy|Doctor of Philosophy]] (PhD) degree in 1986.<ref name="whoswho">{{Who's Who | author=Anon| surname = Durrant-Whyte | othernames = Prof. Hugh Francis | id = U251082 | year = 2017 | doi =10.1093/ww/9780199540884.013.251082 | edition = online [[Oxford_University_Press|Oxford University Press]]|location=Oxford}} {{subscription required}}</ref> He was a [[Thouron_Award|Thouron Scholar]] in 1983.<ref name=":0">{{cite web |url=http://www.thouronaward.org/docs/thouronnewssu07.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2012-02-06 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140814043625/http://www.thouronaward.org/docs/thouronnewssu07.pdf |archivedate=14 August 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>
== 职业发展与科学研究 ==
From 1986 to 1987, Durrant-Whyte was a [[BP|BP]] [[research_fellow|research fellow]] in the [[Department_of_Engineering_Science,_University_of_Oxford|Department of Engineering Science]], [[University_of_Oxford|University of Oxford]], and a [[Fellow_(Oxbridge)|Fellow]] of [[St_Cross_College,_Oxford|St Cross College, Oxford]]. Then, from 1987 to 1995, he was a Fellow of [[Oriel_College,_Oxford|Oriel College, Oxford]], and a [[Lecturer|university lecturer]] in [[engineering_science|engineering science]].<ref name=whoswho />

1995年，他在[[悉尼大学|悉尼大学]]担任[[机电工程|机电工程]][[教授|教授]]。<ref name=whoswho />1999年到2002年期间，他还担任[[澳大利亚野外机器人中心|澳大利亚野外机器人中心]](ACFR)主任。From 2002 until 2010 he held the position of Research Director of the [[Australian_Research_Council|Australian Research Council]] Centre of Excellence for Autonomous Systems (CAS), a joint venture between the ACFR and mechatronics groups at the [[University_of_Technology,_Sydney|University of Technology, Sydney]] and the [[University_of_New_South_Wales|University of New South Wales]]. He was elected as a [[Fellow_of_the_Royal_Society|Fellow of the Royal Society]] in 2010. Hugh has published more than 350 research papers, graduated more than 70 PhD students, and won numerous awards and prizes for his work. He played a critical role in raising the visibility of Australian robotics internationally and was named "Professional Engineer of the year" (2008) by the Institute of Engineers Australia Sydney Division and NSW "Scientist of the Year" (2010).<ref>World-leading robotics engineer named NSW Scientist of the Year - University of Sydney [http://sydney.edu.au/news/84.html?newsstoryid=5637]</ref>

Durrant-Whyte is one of the early pioneers of [[SLAM|SLAM]] with [[John_J._Leonard|John J. Leonard]]. Durrant-Whyte became the CEO of [[NICTA|NICTA]] on 13 December 2010. He resigned as NICTA CEO on 28 November 2014 citing differences with the Board over future funding arrangements.

He was appointed as the [[Chief_Scientific_Adviser_to_the_Ministry_of_Defence|Chief Scientific Adviser]] at the UK [[Ministry_of_Defence_(United_Kingdom)|Ministry of Defence]] on 27 February 2017.<ref>https://www.gov.uk/government/news/defence-secretary-announces-world-class-innovation-panel</ref> As a dual citizen with Australian and British citizenship, Durrant-Whyte was barred from overseeing the UK's nuclear weapons programme.<ref>{{cite web |title=Australian-UK dual national scientist Hugh Durrant-Whyte barred from nuclear duties |accessdate=March 28, 2018 |url=https://www.smh.com.au/world/australianuk-dual-national-scientist-hugh-durrantwhyte-stripped-of-nuclear-duties-20171120-gzon08.html |date=December 20, 2017 }}</ref>

In May 2018 Durrant-Whyte was appointed NSW Chief Scientist & Engineer by [[Gladys_Berejiklian|Gladys Berejiklian]], NSW Premier. He took up his appointment on 3 September 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.chiefscientist.nsw.gov.au/latest-news/new-nsw-chief-scientist-and-engineer-announced|title=New NSW Chief Scientist & Engineer appointed|date=2018-05-29|website=NSW Chief Scientist & Engineer|access-date=2018-12-09}}</ref>

